---
import PublicLayout from '../../layouts/PublicLayout.astro';
---

<PublicLayout
  title="Getting started — Mnema docs"
  description="A 5-minute tour of Mnema: create a doc, invite a teammate, search, autocomplete, connect Claude."
  pathname="/docs/getting-started"
>
  <article class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-6 pt-[80px] pb-[96px]">
    <a
      href="/docs"
      class="transition-colors inline-block mb-8"
      style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-tertiary);"
      onmouseover="this.style.color='var(--text-primary)'"
      onmouseout="this.style.color='var(--text-tertiary)'"
    >
      ← All docs
    </a>

    <span
      class="block mb-3 font-mono uppercase"
      style="font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--text-tertiary);"
    >
      Getting started
    </span>
    <h1
      style="font-size: 28px; line-height: 1.3; letter-spacing: -0.01em; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary);"
    >
      Getting started
    </h1>
    <p
      class="mt-3 mb-12"
      style="font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary);"
    >
      A 5-minute tour. By the end, your team has a working doc and Claude can read it.
    </p>

    <ol class="space-y-8 list-none">
      {[
        {
          heading: 'Create your first doc',
          body: (
            <span>
              From <a href="/app" style="color: var(--text-primary);" class="underline">your workspace</a>, click{' '}
              <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">New doc</span>. Give it a title. Start typing — Mnema
              is a live markdown editor. Press{' '}
              <code style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; background: var(--surface-sunken); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 2px 6px; color: var(--text-primary);">/</code>
              {' '}to insert blocks: headings, code, math, mermaid diagrams.
            </span>
          ),
        },
        {
          heading: 'Invite a teammate',
          body: (
            <span>
              Open <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">Settings → Members</span> and send an invite by email.
              They get a magic link that lands them straight in the workspace. Roles:{' '}
              <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">owner</span> manages billing and people,{' '}
              <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">editor</span> writes and comments,{' '}
              <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">viewer</span> reads.
            </span>
          ),
        },
        {
          heading: 'Try search',
          body: (
            <span>
              Hybrid search runs over every doc in the workspace. Search for an exact phrase, a topic, or a
              question. Results rank by both keyword match and semantic similarity — typing{' '}
              <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">"rate limiting"</span> surfaces docs about throttling
              even if they don't use the exact phrase.
            </span>
          ),
        },
        {
          heading: 'Use autocomplete',
          body: (
            <span>
              As you type, Mnema suggests how a sentence could continue based on the surrounding doc. Press{' '}
              <code style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; background: var(--surface-sunken); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 2px 6px; color: var(--text-primary);">Tab</code>
              {' '}to accept the suggestion, or just keep typing to dismiss it. Autocomplete is included on Pro and Team plans.
            </span>
          ),
        },
        {
          heading: 'Connect Claude and (next) build a flow',
          body: (
            <span>
              Open <a href="/docs/connect" style="color: var(--text-primary);" class="underline">Connect to Claude</a> and follow the 30-second setup.
              Once your Claude connector is active, Claude can read every doc in your workspace through MCP.
              The <a href="/docs/flows" style="color: var(--text-primary);" class="underline">next release adds flows</a> — sequenced content with step-by-step instructions —
              for when "read everything" isn't precise enough.
            </span>
          ),
        },
      ].map((step, i) => (
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center font-mono font-medium"
            style="width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--surface-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border-default); font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-primary);"
          >
            {i + 1}
          </div>
          <div class="pt-0.5">
            <h2 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 4px;">
              {step.heading}
            </h2>
            <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65;">
              {step.body}
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>

    <div
      class="mt-16 p-6"
      style="background: var(--surface-overlay); border: 1px solid var(--border-default); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);"
    >
      <h3 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 8px;">
        What's next
      </h3>
      <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65;">
        Explore <a href="/docs/connect" class="underline" style="color: var(--text-primary);">the connector setup</a>, browse{' '}
        <a href="/pricing" class="underline" style="color: var(--text-primary);">the pricing tiers</a> when your team grows past the free limits,
        or just keep writing — Mnema gets out of the way and lets the docs do the work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</PublicLayout>
